<h2>Security and Privacy Considerations</h2>
<p>ChatGPT extensions send your data to third-party servers. Consider these risks:</p>
<p><strong>Privacy checklist:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>[ ] Read the extension's privacy policy</li>
<li>[ ] Check what data is collected and how it is used</li>
<li>[ ] Avoid extensions that require unnecessary permissions</li>
<li>[ ] Be cautious with extensions on sensitive pages (banking, health)</li>
<li>[ ] Remove extensions you no longer use</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Red flags:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Extensions requesting access to all websites without clear reason</li>
<li>No privacy policy or vague data usage terms</li>
<li>Extensions from unknown developers with few reviews</li>
</ul>
<h2>Common Extension Problems</h2>
<p><strong>Slow performance:</strong> Extensions that inject content into every page can slow browsing. Disable extensions you are not actively using.</p>
<p><strong>Conflicts:</strong> Running multiple ChatGPT extensions simultaneously can cause conflicts. Choose one primary extension.</p>
<p><strong>API costs:</strong> Some extensions use your OpenAI API key. Heavy use can generate unexpected charges. Monitor your API usage.</p>
<p><strong>Outdated extensions:</strong> ChatGPT updates frequently. Extensions that are not maintained may break. Check the last update date before installing.</p>
