<h2>FAQ</h2>
<p><strong>Are ChatGPT Chrome extensions safe?</strong></p>
<p>Most are safe if from reputable developers, but they send your browsing data to third parties. Read privacy policies, check reviews, and avoid extensions with excessive permissions.</p>
<p><strong>Do I need ChatGPT Plus to use these extensions?</strong></p>
<p>Some extensions work with the free ChatGPT tier. Others require an API key or ChatGPT Plus subscription. Check the requirements before installing.</p>
<p><strong>Which ChatGPT extension is best for writing?</strong></p>
<p>Compose AI and ChatGPT Writer are the best for writing assistance. Compose AI offers autocomplete across text fields. ChatGPT Writer specializes in email composition.</p>
<p><strong>Can extensions access my personal data?</strong></p>
<p>Extensions with broad permissions can see page content. Be cautious about which extensions you grant access to sensitive sites like email, banking, or health portals.</p>
<p><strong>Do these extensions work with Claude or Gemini?</strong></p>
<p>Some extensions support multiple models. Merlin, ChatGPT for Google, and ChatGPT Sidebar support Claude and Gemini in addition to ChatGPT.</p>
<p><strong>Why use an extension instead of the ChatGPT website?</strong></p>
<p>Extensions bring AI into your existing workflow without switching tabs. This saves time when you need quick assistance while reading, writing, or researching on the web.</p>
